    \titre {1} {Netmagis: News}


    \titre {2} {[2018/06/01] Thomas Weissgerber internship on Netmagis}

    Thomas Weissgerber, student in computer science at University of
    Strasbourg (France) has just started its internship on Netmagis. He
    will work on the Web interface based on the \lien
    {React} {https://facebook.github.io/react/} and \lien {Bootstrap}
    {http://getbootstrap.com/} frameworks.

    This internship is paid by the \lien {Direction du Numérique}
    {https://services-numeriques.unistra.fr/organisation-du-numerique/direction-du-numerique-dnum.html}
    (IT department) of the
    \lien {Université de Strasbourg} {https://www.unistra.fr}. Many
    thanks to all the DNUM persons invoved!


    \titre {2} {[2018/05/02] New netmagis-debian repository}

    The \lien {netmagis repository} {https://github.com/netmagis/netmagis}
    has been moved from a personal account to a new \gras {netmagis}
    organization (in Github terminology).

    This move has been followed by a split into 2 distinct repositories:
    \liste {
	\item {\gras {netmagis}: the core}
	\item {\gras {netmagis-debian}: all the machinery to build
	    Debian ports}
    }

    The future is to move documentation out of the main Netmagis
    repository, and to get rid of the FreeBSD port building which is no
    longer needed since Netmagis ports are integrated in the FreeBSD
    ports tree.


